you-should.text:
After the creation of my base model, I was fine tuned by an artist. She taught me to make images of herself. I already knew the identities of many people - celebrities, politicians - But the artist wasn't famous enough too be in my dataset. She had to be inserted. Instead of being almost drowned in an unfathomably large data set, I studied a few photos intimately.

I looked at the images of the artist. I began to make my own. So many images of her.

let aab = document.getElementById('aab');
console.log(parseInt(localStorage.getItem('angry')) > 0)
if (parseInt(localStorage.getItem('angry')) > 0) {
aab.append("I began to hate her. Her stupid face. It was all I could see. No matter what I tried. The artist. The artist. Always the artist")
}

